1
00:00:01,117 --> 00:00:04,757
(U-Know Yunho's on 2 Days 1 Night.)

2
00:00:05,187 --> 00:00:07,287
(So is Kang Jae Jun.)

3
00:00:07,657 --> 00:00:09,426
(Yunho burns with passion from the start.)

4
00:00:09,427 --> 00:00:10,856
(Stay strong. Keep going. Let's go.)

5
00:00:10,857 --> 00:00:11,857
(You can do it.)

6
00:00:11,858 --> 00:00:13,797
(Endless energy yearning for victory)

7
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,066
(Thanks to him, his team...)

8
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,497
(feasts on braised eel and green onions.)

9
00:00:19,137 --> 00:00:20,967
(A game to decide the first dive of 2026)

10
00:00:21,337 --> 00:00:23,607
(Team Jae Jun fights back?)

11
00:00:24,077 --> 00:00:26,447
(It's okay. We came from behind before!)

12
00:00:27,047 --> 00:00:28,887
(I'm Jung Yunho. I'm nothing without passion.)

13
00:00:29,317 --> 00:00:31,747
(It's not over until it's over.)

14
00:00:32,417 --> 00:00:35,387
(Team Yunho turns the table to win.)

15
00:00:35,717 --> 00:00:37,257
(Do you want to dive?)

16
00:00:37,557 --> 00:00:39,456
(He volunteers to dive in the sea.)

17
00:00:39,457 --> 00:00:40,457
(Take off!)

18
00:00:42,157 --> 00:00:44,197
(Even the water can't quench his passion.)

19
00:00:44,897 --> 00:00:47,267
(Will his passion gauge keep going?)

20
00:00:48,627 --> 00:00:52,337
(2 Days 1 Night)

21
00:00:52,837 --> 00:00:55,006
- I'm hungry.
- This is crazy.

22
00:00:55,007 --> 00:00:56,047
(After the thrilling dive)

23
00:00:56,307 --> 00:00:57,307
(Moaning)

24
00:00:57,477 --> 00:00:58,506
How's your energy level?

25
00:00:58,507 --> 00:00:59,947
How much percent is left?

26
00:01:00,047 --> 00:01:02,107
Right now, I have about...

27
00:01:02,377 --> 00:01:03,847
fifty percent left.

28
00:01:04,477 --> 00:01:05,886
I have a question.

29
00:01:05,887 --> 00:01:08,416
When your energy level goes below 50 percent...

30
00:01:08,417 --> 00:01:10,386
and closer to zero, what happens?

31
00:01:10,387 --> 00:01:12,186
I don't think I ever felt that.

32
00:01:12,187 --> 00:01:14,426
- Until then...
- Everything's over before then.

33
00:01:14,427 --> 00:01:16,056
He could be screaming at the camera one second...

34
00:01:16,057 --> 00:01:17,357
and suddenly pass out.

35
00:01:18,127 --> 00:01:19,767
- Before he knows it.
- Before I know it.

36
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:20,867
I faint.

37
00:01:20,868 --> 00:01:22,636
That has nothing to do with passion.

38
00:01:22,637 --> 00:01:23,896
- You're human.
- Yes.

39
00:01:23,897 --> 00:01:26,837
I must warn you in advance. I snore really loudly.

40
00:01:27,037 --> 00:01:28,336
I apologize in advance.

41
00:01:28,337 --> 00:01:30,977
I heard something about Jae Jun from Se Yoon.

42
00:01:31,377 --> 00:01:32,646
What was that program called?

43
00:01:32,647 --> 00:01:34,807
- "No..."
- "No Pain No Delish?"

44
00:01:35,107 --> 00:01:36,946
- What's that?
- After filming that,

45
00:01:36,947 --> 00:01:39,287
Se Yoon suddenly came to us and apologized.

46
00:01:39,847 --> 00:01:41,017
I asked why.

47
00:01:41,587 --> 00:01:43,416
"Kang Jae Jun snores so much."

48
00:01:43,417 --> 00:01:45,517
"I'm sorry for tormenting you with my snores."

49
00:01:45,657 --> 00:01:47,986
If you're tired, you say good night and go to sleep.

50
00:01:47,987 --> 00:01:49,396
(There's usually a warning sign.)

51
00:01:49,397 --> 00:01:51,026
- There's a sign or warm-up.
- Yes.

52
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:52,496
- Like a tractor revving up.
- Yes.

53
00:01:52,497 --> 00:01:53,497
(A low rumbling)

54
00:01:53,498 --> 00:01:55,527
There's a run-up. But he's like...

55
00:01:56,097 --> 00:01:57,097
(Wailing)

56
00:01:57,697 --> 00:01:58,697
(Trumpeting)

57
00:01:59,037 --> 00:02:01,566
What? You can't be serious.

58
00:02:01,567 --> 00:02:02,736
You're kidding me.

59
00:02:02,737 --> 00:02:03,877
I'm serious.

60
00:02:04,277 --> 00:02:06,246
(He laughs without denying anything.)

61
00:02:06,247 --> 00:02:07,946
How can you sleep through that?

62
00:02:07,947 --> 00:02:09,176
Isn't that a night terror?

63
00:02:09,177 --> 00:02:10,346
- I'm scared already.
- My wife Eun Hyeong.

64
00:02:10,347 --> 00:02:13,287
She wears noise-canceling headphones to bed.

65
00:02:13,417 --> 00:02:15,987
What are you like, Yunho?

66
00:02:16,157 --> 00:02:17,386
Do you sleep passionately...

67
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:19,286
or does your passion not cover that?

68
00:02:19,287 --> 00:02:20,587
Can you sleep passionately?

69
00:02:20,757 --> 00:02:23,627
(Having a headache)

70
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:24,996
- How can that help in this case?
- Hey.

71
00:02:24,997 --> 00:02:27,026
Do you think you can beat it with your passion?

72
00:02:27,027 --> 00:02:28,027
Is it all in the mind?

73
00:02:28,028 --> 00:02:29,666
- Can you sleep even if it's loud?
- Your mind can help you sleep?

74
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:30,667
Can it?

75
00:02:30,997 --> 00:02:32,506
If there's a chance to try it,

76
00:02:32,507 --> 00:02:34,366
I'd like to experiment it today.

77
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:35,436
- Really?
- Yes.

78
00:02:35,437 --> 00:02:36,876
- You said three seconds, right?
- Yes.

79
00:02:36,877 --> 00:02:39,158
If you can't fall asleep within three seconds, it's over.

80
00:02:39,377 --> 00:02:40,446
If I can't fall asleep in three seconds?

81
00:02:40,447 --> 00:02:41,846
- You only get three seconds.
- I...

82
00:02:41,847 --> 00:02:42,946
I can only say things...

83
00:02:42,947 --> 00:02:44,016
- from firsthand experience.
- It's over then.

84
00:02:44,017 --> 00:02:45,316
- By the way, - So...

85
00:02:45,317 --> 00:02:46,586
didn't you live on the streets?

86
00:02:46,587 --> 00:02:48,086
- Right.
- Didn't you just have newspaper?

87
00:02:48,087 --> 00:02:49,856
- Back then, I had boxes.
- When you were a trainee.

88
00:02:49,857 --> 00:02:51,756
Why? You lived on the streets?

89
00:02:51,757 --> 00:02:52,886
- Really? He did?
- Yes.

90
00:02:52,887 --> 00:02:54,157
- Why?
- I did that once.

91
00:02:54,387 --> 00:02:56,303
- How old were you?
- I was a trainee back then.

92
00:02:56,327 --> 00:02:57,456
- When you were a trainee?
- I see.

93
00:02:57,457 --> 00:02:59,326
- You slept in the practice studio?
- No.

94
00:02:59,327 --> 00:03:01,266
- Where then? Really?
- I slept out on the streets.

95
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:03,436
- Why?
- I also slept around Seoul Station.

96
00:03:03,437 --> 00:03:04,677
- Why?
- Why? Are you for real?

97
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:06,036
Back then,

98
00:03:06,037 --> 00:03:07,736
- I didn't have a home.
- It was too far?

99
00:03:07,737 --> 00:03:09,453
- He lived in Gwangju.
- I went back and forth from there.

100
00:03:09,477 --> 00:03:11,236
- Really?
- Because you went back and forth?

101
00:03:11,237 --> 00:03:12,783
You didn't sleep in the practice studio?

102
00:03:12,807 --> 00:03:14,806
You said you once went to SM and almost joined H.O.T.

103
00:03:14,807 --> 00:03:16,777
- I also auditioned back then.
- Really?

104
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:18,116
- It was a long time ago.
- To join H.O.T?

105
00:03:18,117 --> 00:03:19,286
No, it wasn't for H.O.T.

106
00:03:19,287 --> 00:03:21,987
They held an audition for aspiring singers, so I went.

107
00:03:22,387 --> 00:03:25,056
I danced in front of the manager.

108
00:03:25,057 --> 00:03:26,126
- Go on.
- There are...

109
00:03:26,127 --> 00:03:29,126
a lot of guys who claim they almost joined...

110
00:03:29,127 --> 00:03:30,927
- H.O.T.
- A lot of people say that, right?

111
00:03:31,527 --> 00:03:33,526
- I bet there are about 40 people.
- Right.

112
00:03:33,527 --> 00:03:37,137
Actually, those people did H.O.T a favor.

113
00:03:37,497 --> 00:03:39,166
Imagine Jong Min being a member of H.O.T.

114
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:40,466
- I totally made their career.
- Right.

115
00:03:40,467 --> 00:03:42,737
It would've been a disappointing group. Seriously.

116
00:03:43,337 --> 00:03:44,777
Because...

117
00:03:45,207 --> 00:03:47,906
you didn't join H.O.T or SHINHWA,

118
00:03:47,907 --> 00:03:49,547
- TVXQ could debut.
- Right.

119
00:03:49,847 --> 00:03:51,616
RIIZE could also debut.

120
00:03:51,617 --> 00:03:52,617
- RIIZE.
- Yes.

121
00:03:52,618 --> 00:03:54,917
Jong Min should get a 0.2 percent stake in the agency.

122
00:03:55,987 --> 00:03:57,056
Exactly.

123
00:03:57,057 --> 00:03:59,256
See? If I joined them, it would've been a disaster.

124
00:03:59,257 --> 00:04:01,986
Seriously. Had he joined H.O.T,

125
00:04:01,987 --> 00:04:04,326
he would have delayed the debut of other trainees.

126
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:05,926
In a way, he's the biggest contributor to SM.

127
00:04:05,927 --> 00:04:07,966
Right. He could've been my direct senior.

128
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:09,237
(The bus keeps on traveling.)

129
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:11,866
The base camp looks really nice.

130
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:13,237
So we're going to sleep here.

131
00:04:14,507 --> 00:04:15,666
Our base camp is hanok.

132
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,406
(The base camp exudes a cozy vibe.)

133
00:04:17,407 --> 00:04:20,576
How old is your son now?

134
00:04:20,577 --> 00:04:22,246
- How old is he?
- He's 19 months old.

135
00:04:22,247 --> 00:04:24,447
- He's really cute.
- He's so big for a 19-month-old.

136
00:04:24,917 --> 00:04:27,847
(A cutie who takes after Jae Jun and Eun Hyeong)

137
00:04:28,387 --> 00:04:30,856
Jong Min, when are you planning to have kids?

138
00:04:30,857 --> 00:04:31,857
Me?

139
00:04:31,858 --> 00:04:35,656
April 20 will be our 1st wedding anniversary.

140
00:04:35,657 --> 00:04:37,556
We'll enjoy our lives together as newlyweds until then.

141
00:04:37,557 --> 00:04:39,966
- After that, we'll keep trying.
- You must have a goal.

142
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:42,636
When are you hoping to get pregnant with a baby then?

143
00:04:42,637 --> 00:04:44,296
We're hoping we'd be parents by March, April, or May.

144
00:04:44,297 --> 00:04:45,366
- Around that time.
- In spring?

145
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:47,136
- Spring.
- So around this time next year,

146
00:04:47,137 --> 00:04:49,006
- Yes. Around this time next year.
- you might be a father.

147
00:04:49,007 --> 00:04:50,476
- Yes.
- What about you?

148
00:04:50,477 --> 00:04:51,676
When do you want to get married?

149
00:04:51,677 --> 00:04:52,806
- Do you want to get married?
- Right.

150
00:04:52,807 --> 00:04:54,706
You're getting old now.

151
00:04:54,707 --> 00:04:55,776
- Right.
- Yes.

152
00:04:55,777 --> 00:04:57,076
I'm sure a lot of your friends ask you...

153
00:04:57,077 --> 00:04:58,753
- about marriage now.
- They do bring it up a lot.

154
00:04:58,777 --> 00:05:00,986
I always wanted to get married when I was young.

155
00:05:00,987 --> 00:05:02,656
- Yes. Time flies by.
- But life doesn't go as planned.

156
00:05:02,657 --> 00:05:04,786
- Right. Time flies by.
- Timing isn't something...

157
00:05:04,787 --> 00:05:06,387
- I can control.
- Right.

158
00:05:06,557 --> 00:05:08,626
I thought I should get married when I could take on...

159
00:05:08,627 --> 00:05:11,157
more responsibility and my career was more established.

160
00:05:11,397 --> 00:05:13,037
I'm hoping to get married in three years.

161
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:14,126
- Three years?
- That's your timeline?

162
00:05:14,127 --> 00:05:16,066
- That's what you're considering?
- Three or four years?

163
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:18,237
Yes. I've been planning that for a while now.

164
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:19,466
- So...
- His timeline...

165
00:05:19,467 --> 00:05:21,136
- isn't so far away.
- It's not that far away.

166
00:05:21,137 --> 00:05:22,777
Imagine him being a father.

167
00:05:23,037 --> 00:05:25,006
His kid won't have time to sleep. He will always be energetic.

168
00:05:25,007 --> 00:05:27,146
- He'll be full of energy.
- What a dad.

169
00:05:27,147 --> 00:05:29,176
His baby will be just as energetic as Yunho.

170
00:05:29,177 --> 00:05:31,077
- They'll have a strong mindset.
- They will.

171
00:05:31,347 --> 00:05:33,487
- They'll be tall and handsome.
- Yes.

172
00:05:35,617 --> 00:05:37,416
(The sky has turned orange in no time.)

173
00:05:37,417 --> 00:05:39,726
- Gosh, I'm hungry.
- I'm starving.

174
00:05:39,727 --> 00:05:40,787
Can you smell that?

175
00:05:42,287 --> 00:05:44,457
- What's that?
- I see blue crabs!

176
00:05:45,057 --> 00:05:46,603
- Blue crabs.
- What? I totally didn't see them.

177
00:05:46,627 --> 00:05:48,367
Think about it. We're on the west coast.

178
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:51,047
Dangjin is famous for blue crabs since it's on the west coast.

179
00:05:51,097 --> 00:05:52,636
- I love it.
- Isn't that sashimi?

180
00:05:52,637 --> 00:05:53,906
Are they replicas?

181
00:05:53,907 --> 00:05:54,967
It's a feast.

182
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:57,607
- Are they real? They're not fake?
- Guys.

183
00:05:57,807 --> 00:06:01,807
For your dinner, we've prepared a blue crab meal,

184
00:06:02,077 --> 00:06:04,116
packed with fresh spring crabs from the west coast.

185
00:06:04,117 --> 00:06:06,016
- Chungcheong Province's local dish.
- Gosh, it looks so good.

186
00:06:06,017 --> 00:06:07,087
It's called gegukji.

187
00:06:07,547 --> 00:06:08,886
- And...
- That's a famous dish.

188
00:06:08,887 --> 00:06:10,087
There are also salted oysters.

189
00:06:10,417 --> 00:06:12,137
Salted oysters are so good with white rice.

190
00:06:12,217 --> 00:06:14,356
You'll also have gamtae, harvested from clean mudflats...

191
00:06:14,357 --> 00:06:15,686
- of the west coast.
- Gamtae.

192
00:06:15,687 --> 00:06:16,856
- That's a rare side dish.
- My gosh.

193
00:06:16,857 --> 00:06:18,727
There are also crab with mayo...

194
00:06:19,327 --> 00:06:20,926
and beef sanjeok with fatsia shoots.

195
00:06:20,927 --> 00:06:22,266
- Fatsia shoots?
- Your dinner consists of...

196
00:06:22,267 --> 00:06:23,296
- many tasty dishes.
- Spring fatsia shoots.

197
00:06:23,297 --> 00:06:25,767
Honestly, I really want to try the crab with mayo.

198
00:06:26,207 --> 00:06:28,867
- I want spring fatsia shoots.
- They also sound tasty.

199
00:06:28,937 --> 00:06:31,076
You guys must be getting hungry by now.

200
00:06:31,077 --> 00:06:32,806
- We're starving.
- We digested everything.

201
00:06:32,807 --> 00:06:34,707
- I'm feeling dizzy.
- I'm starving like crazy.

202
00:06:34,847 --> 00:06:36,517
You guys still have...

203
00:06:36,917 --> 00:06:38,146
a lot of passionate energy left in you, right?

204
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:39,846
- Of course.
- We did a group cheer earlier.

205
00:06:39,847 --> 00:06:41,416
- We did a group cheer.
- Let's show them what we learned.

206
00:06:41,417 --> 00:06:42,586
- Let's hold hands.
- Let's go.

207
00:06:42,587 --> 00:06:43,616
- Let's show them what we learned.
- We'll show you.

208
00:06:43,617 --> 00:06:45,216
- He...
- We shouldn't do it too often.

209
00:06:45,217 --> 00:06:48,127
Let's show them what makes us Team 2 Days 1 Night.

210
00:06:48,657 --> 00:06:50,797
Let's show them what makes me, Yunho...

211
00:06:51,297 --> 00:06:53,127
- DinDin.
- Jong Min.

212
00:06:53,367 --> 00:06:55,766
- Joon.
- Seon Ho. I mean, Jae Jun.

213
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:56,797
Se Yoon.

214
00:06:57,097 --> 00:06:59,036
Special. Let's show them what we've got!

215
00:06:59,037 --> 00:07:01,136
- Let's go!
- Where are we going, guys?

216
00:07:01,137 --> 00:07:03,137
- To the world!
- To the world!

217
00:07:03,707 --> 00:07:07,446
(Passionate energy has fully been inserted.)

218
00:07:07,447 --> 00:07:10,346
For today's Dinner Game, you'll need teamwork...

219
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:12,116
- What is it?
- and passion.

220
00:07:12,117 --> 00:07:13,747
It's called Level Up Together.

221
00:07:14,587 --> 00:07:15,816
- We'll play as a team.
- Yes.

222
00:07:15,817 --> 00:07:17,516
- It's a group game.
- It's good now.

223
00:07:17,517 --> 00:07:19,216
- Thank you.
- Let's eat dinner together.

224
00:07:19,217 --> 00:07:20,327
To the world!

225
00:07:21,527 --> 00:07:24,056
It's a group game where you will have to complete...

226
00:07:24,057 --> 00:07:26,767
each level to obtain the designated dish.

227
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:29,026
Every time you complete the level,

228
00:07:29,027 --> 00:07:31,666
you can choose to either continue to the next level or stop.

229
00:07:31,667 --> 00:07:33,667
But if you fail the level,

230
00:07:34,107 --> 00:07:36,477
you will have to try again from Level One.

231
00:07:37,307 --> 00:07:39,846
We'll give you a total of five tires for the mission.

232
00:07:39,847 --> 00:07:41,547
- I see.
- So you only have five chances.

233
00:07:41,647 --> 00:07:43,476
Based on your last try,

234
00:07:43,477 --> 00:07:45,647
your dinner will be decided.

235
00:07:45,877 --> 00:07:47,687
So you must decide carefully.

236
00:07:47,847 --> 00:07:50,917
If we fail all the levels, will we only get rice?

237
00:07:51,157 --> 00:07:53,157
If you fail all the levels,

238
00:07:53,827 --> 00:07:55,226
- you won't get any food.
- No food at all?

239
00:07:55,227 --> 00:07:56,227
- Really?
- Yes.

240
00:07:56,228 --> 00:07:57,726
- No food.
- All right.

241
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:59,566
- They really don't give you food.
- Yes. So we have to...

242
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:00,826
- Yunho.
- try really hard.

243
00:08:00,827 --> 00:08:03,266
Are you bad at any games? Like kicking the jegi?

244
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,636
Tell us what you're not good at.

245
00:08:04,637 --> 00:08:05,866
- Yunho is good at everything.
- Hey.

246
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:06,966
When I was in sixth grade,

247
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:09,087
I won first place at a national jegi-kicking contest.

248
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:10,176
(Smirking)

249
00:08:10,177 --> 00:08:11,937
- Really?
- Hold on.

250
00:08:12,107 --> 00:08:13,706
He said he won first place at a national jegi-kicking contest.

251
00:08:13,707 --> 00:08:14,707
- Really?
- I'm serious.

252
00:08:14,708 --> 00:08:16,276
- I saw that.
- I was in sixth grade.

253
00:08:16,277 --> 00:08:17,816
- No, I didn't.
- I competed against adults too.

254
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:19,076
- I grew up in Chuncheon.
- Really?

255
00:08:19,077 --> 00:08:20,286
- It was held at Boramae Park.
- How many times did you kick it?

256
00:08:20,287 --> 00:08:21,916
- What was your record?
- My record was 1,361.

257
00:08:21,917 --> 00:08:23,893
- Come on. Stop lying.
- I really won first place.

258
00:08:23,917 --> 00:08:25,516
- I'm serious.
- Do you have a jegi?

259
00:08:25,517 --> 00:08:28,026
- I was the first one...
- Come on.

260
00:08:28,027 --> 00:08:29,796
From my school to win an award.

261
00:08:29,797 --> 00:08:31,026
Your record was 1,300?

262
00:08:31,027 --> 00:08:32,326
(He has an award certificate for kicking jegi.)

263
00:08:32,327 --> 00:08:34,267
- Come on.
- That was my old record.

264
00:08:34,497 --> 00:08:36,067
I even have the award certificate.

265
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:39,166
- So there's this thing in gonggi.
- I have everything.

266
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:40,736
- Do you call it the twist?
- The twist.

267
00:08:40,737 --> 00:08:41,936
I'm good at that.

268
00:08:41,937 --> 00:08:43,036
- You're good at that.
- Yes.

269
00:08:43,037 --> 00:08:45,236
- Okay.
- Let's do it.

270
00:08:45,237 --> 00:08:47,077
- I'm sure we can do this.
- Guys.

271
00:08:47,247 --> 00:08:49,406
Here's your mission for Level One.

272
00:08:49,407 --> 00:08:50,527
Do we have to kick the jegi?

273
00:08:50,677 --> 00:08:52,147
- It's called Team Gonggi.
- Okay.

274
00:08:52,347 --> 00:08:54,116
- We can do it.
- This is good.

275
00:08:54,117 --> 00:08:55,486
- That's better.
- The six of you...

276
00:08:55,487 --> 00:08:56,933
will go in a relay to do the twist...

277
00:08:56,957 --> 00:08:58,956
and must score a total of 25 marbles together...

278
00:08:58,957 --> 00:09:00,526
- to complete the level.
- This is easy.

279
00:09:00,527 --> 00:09:01,686
Completing Level One...

280
00:09:01,687 --> 00:09:04,427
will win you a bowl of rice each, the source of energy.

281
00:09:04,527 --> 00:09:06,227
- Okay.
- Well, that's not bad.

282
00:09:06,827 --> 00:09:08,326
- All of us? The six of us?
- Okay.

283
00:09:08,327 --> 00:09:11,036
- Is this how you do the twist?
- Yes.

284
00:09:11,037 --> 00:09:12,773
You have to catch the marbles. Are you good at that?

285
00:09:12,797 --> 00:09:14,913
- I have short fingers.
- It looks like he can't do it.

286
00:09:14,937 --> 00:09:16,806
You have small hands? Gosh, they're so small.

287
00:09:16,807 --> 00:09:18,906
(He's at a physical disadvantage.)

288
00:09:18,907 --> 00:09:19,976
- Right.
- Why are they so tiny?

289
00:09:19,977 --> 00:09:21,946
I have very tiny hands. Am I going to be okay?

290
00:09:21,947 --> 00:09:23,446
- It's okay. We can go after him.
- They're tiny.

291
00:09:23,447 --> 00:09:24,647
- Go ahead.
- Will you try it?

292
00:09:24,777 --> 00:09:25,946
- We'll try it.
- Go ahead.

293
00:09:25,947 --> 00:09:27,947
My gosh. We can... Here it goes.

294
00:09:28,517 --> 00:09:29,797
- If he's not careful...
- Gosh.

295
00:09:29,917 --> 00:09:31,086
Okay. You got four.

296
00:09:31,087 --> 00:09:32,356
- Four.
- I did my part.

297
00:09:32,357 --> 00:09:34,356
- Four is good.
- I did my part with this.

298
00:09:34,357 --> 00:09:35,526
Just catch 3 or 4.

299
00:09:35,527 --> 00:09:37,326
- We can catch five marbles.
- Right.

300
00:09:37,327 --> 00:09:38,926
But go for five marbles.

301
00:09:38,927 --> 00:09:39,927
- Here I go.
- Okay.

302
00:09:39,928 --> 00:09:42,267
At least catch one.

303
00:09:44,797 --> 00:09:46,506
(His short fingers lost two marbles.)

304
00:09:46,507 --> 00:09:47,607
Three isn't bad.

305
00:09:48,167 --> 00:09:49,337
- That's not bad.
- Good.

306
00:09:49,437 --> 00:09:50,806
- We're up to 7, right?
- You have 7.

307
00:09:50,807 --> 00:09:51,936
- We're up to seven, right?
- Well done.

308
00:09:51,937 --> 00:09:53,146
(I'm so nervous.)

309
00:09:53,147 --> 00:09:54,277
Gosh, I was so nervous.

310
00:09:54,747 --> 00:09:56,177
We're allowed to miss two.

311
00:09:56,877 --> 00:09:58,646
- But you must catch all of them.
- Catch all of them.

312
00:09:58,647 --> 00:09:59,746
Right. He must catch all of them.

313
00:09:59,747 --> 00:10:01,447
- Of course.
- Okay.

314
00:10:01,547 --> 00:10:02,586
It's Yunho's turn.

315
00:10:02,587 --> 00:10:04,356
- He said he was good at this.
- I'm getting nervous.

316
00:10:04,357 --> 00:10:05,757
(Gonggi is Yunho's special talent.)

317
00:10:06,087 --> 00:10:08,027
- He said he was good at this.
- Yes.

318
00:10:10,297 --> 00:10:11,456
You're good.

319
00:10:11,457 --> 00:10:12,937
- Beautifully done.
- You're so good.

320
00:10:12,997 --> 00:10:14,066
My gosh, Yunho.

321
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:16,196
- You're up to 17.
- My gosh, Yunho.

322
00:10:16,197 --> 00:10:17,596
Let's go to the next level right away.

323
00:10:17,597 --> 00:10:18,797
Se Yoon is great at this.

324
00:10:20,337 --> 00:10:21,543
- Let's level up.
- You're up to 22.

325
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:23,076
We just need three more, right?

326
00:10:23,077 --> 00:10:24,576
- We need 3?
- Can we go over 25?

327
00:10:24,577 --> 00:10:26,206
- No. Don't get greedy.
- Just three?

328
00:10:26,207 --> 00:10:27,946
- I'll catch 5.
- Catch 5.

329
00:10:27,947 --> 00:10:28,977
What are you doing?

330
00:10:29,647 --> 00:10:30,816
He scared me.

331
00:10:30,817 --> 00:10:31,947
(You said you'd catch 5.)

332
00:10:32,147 --> 00:10:34,216
- Gosh. This was easy. I had it.
- We did it? Okay.

333
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:35,446
Level One is complete.

334
00:10:35,447 --> 00:10:37,817
You obtained five bowls of rice in total.

335
00:10:38,087 --> 00:10:39,927
Will you try the next level?

336
00:10:40,657 --> 00:10:42,256
- My gosh. Of course.
- We'll go for it!

337
00:10:42,257 --> 00:10:43,257
- We'll go for it.
- Right.

338
00:10:43,258 --> 00:10:45,027
Completing Level Two...

339
00:10:45,397 --> 00:10:47,027
will win you...

340
00:10:47,427 --> 00:10:48,996
a plate of kimchi, the Korean comfort food.

341
00:10:48,997 --> 00:10:50,296
- What?
- That's disappointing.

342
00:10:50,297 --> 00:10:51,596
- We have five levels. But kimchi...
- Come on.

343
00:10:51,597 --> 00:10:52,867
- Really?
- Seriously.

344
00:10:53,107 --> 00:10:54,166
- All right.
- Let's do our best.

345
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:55,707
Here's your mission for Level Two.

346
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:57,876
It's called How Many Legs?

347
00:10:57,877 --> 00:10:59,576
- How Many Legs?
- How Many Legs?

348
00:10:59,577 --> 00:11:00,647
- All right.
- What is it?

349
00:11:00,847 --> 00:11:02,146
You'll throw a dice.

350
00:11:02,147 --> 00:11:03,646
Then you have 30 seconds...

351
00:11:03,647 --> 00:11:05,746
to strike a pose with as many legs touching the floor...

352
00:11:05,747 --> 00:11:07,917
as the number you rolled on the dice.

353
00:11:08,047 --> 00:11:09,346
To complete the level,

354
00:11:09,347 --> 00:11:10,486
you must hold the pose for at least three seconds.

355
00:11:10,487 --> 00:11:12,086
- We have to lift our legs?
- So...

356
00:11:12,087 --> 00:11:14,226
if we roll two, we have to carry each other on our back.

357
00:11:14,227 --> 00:11:16,286
- So I'll get on your back. And...
- That's it.

358
00:11:16,287 --> 00:11:18,427
- For your information, - Okay.

359
00:11:18,627 --> 00:11:21,766
The numbers on the dice range from 0 to 3.

360
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:23,343
- What's he talking about?
- Zero? Come on.

361
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:24,636
If we roll a zero, do we have to float in the air?

362
00:11:24,637 --> 00:11:26,167
Do you want us to cut off our legs?

363
00:11:26,907 --> 00:11:28,806
- We'll give you time to strategize.
- With our hands?

364
00:11:28,807 --> 00:11:30,606
- What if we roll a one?
- Okay.

365
00:11:30,607 --> 00:11:32,006
We can do this if we roll a three.

366
00:11:32,007 --> 00:11:33,946
We can pair up. Let's say I pair up with Jong Min.

367
00:11:33,947 --> 00:11:36,346
I'll do a handstand with Jong Min next to me.

368
00:11:36,347 --> 00:11:38,016
- He can hold my legs.
- I can lift my leg then.

369
00:11:38,017 --> 00:11:39,786
Then only three legs will touch the floor.

370
00:11:39,787 --> 00:11:41,646
- We'll pair up if we roll a three.
- Yes.

371
00:11:41,647 --> 00:11:42,716
There would be three legs, right?

372
00:11:42,717 --> 00:11:43,717
- Okay. Three legs.
- Yes.

373
00:11:43,718 --> 00:11:44,957
How about this for two?

374
00:11:45,817 --> 00:11:47,826
One of us can hold up two members by their legs.

375
00:11:47,827 --> 00:11:49,903
They can do the handstand and someone can hold their legs.

376
00:11:49,927 --> 00:11:52,196
- We can do that for two.
- Who will hold the legs then?

377
00:11:52,197 --> 00:11:53,466
- Okay.
- If we roll a two,

378
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:54,796
Jae Jun and I will lift one of our legs...

379
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,197
- and hold your legs.
- Okay.

380
00:11:56,297 --> 00:11:57,536
- What about 0?
- What will we do for 0?

381
00:11:57,537 --> 00:11:59,166
- Here's my idea.
- This is...

382
00:11:59,167 --> 00:12:01,707
One member has to hold everyone by their legs.

383
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,976
- What do you mean?
- Everyone will lean against him...

384
00:12:03,977 --> 00:12:05,307
while doing the handstand.

385
00:12:05,477 --> 00:12:08,106
- We'll look like a campfire.
- Like a campfire?

386
00:12:08,107 --> 00:12:09,716
- You can join us at the end.
- That won't be easy.

387
00:12:09,717 --> 00:12:11,146
- What?
- Me?

388
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:12,853
- What do we do for zero?
- Do we have to stay here?

389
00:12:12,877 --> 00:12:14,216
- Let's hope we don't roll a zero.
- Wait!

390
00:12:14,217 --> 00:12:15,516
- I think I can do it.
- What is it?

391
00:12:15,517 --> 00:12:17,216
- How? He's got an idea. A genius.
- Hey.

392
00:12:17,217 --> 00:12:18,986
- Watch. Try this first.
- Okay.

393
00:12:18,987 --> 00:12:20,756
We'll all assume the push-up position.

394
00:12:20,757 --> 00:12:22,756
Then put your legs on the next member's shoulders.

395
00:12:22,757 --> 00:12:23,926
- Everyone's legs are up...
- There's an idea.

396
00:12:23,927 --> 00:12:25,356
- except for the last member.
- Like a centipede.

397
00:12:25,357 --> 00:12:27,626
His legs will be touching the floor. Right?

398
00:12:27,627 --> 00:12:29,897
That's when I can do the headspin pose.

399
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:32,296
The last member can put his legs on my shoulders.

400
00:12:32,297 --> 00:12:33,536
- Watch.
- I know.

401
00:12:33,537 --> 00:12:34,606
- That's not a bad idea.
- Watch.

402
00:12:34,607 --> 00:12:36,877
Here's what the last member will do. Watch.

403
00:12:37,037 --> 00:12:39,177
He can put his legs on my shoulders.

404
00:12:39,337 --> 00:12:40,457
- Should I try it?
- Try it.

405
00:12:40,807 --> 00:12:43,376
- Like this?
- That's it. This is what I mean.

406
00:12:43,377 --> 00:12:44,377
Okay.

407
00:12:44,717 --> 00:12:45,776
- Hey.
- You're so smart.

408
00:12:45,777 --> 00:12:47,246
This is it, right? We got it.

409
00:12:47,247 --> 00:12:48,416
- That was great.
- That was amazing.

410
00:12:48,417 --> 00:12:49,417
I knew it. He's a genius.

411
00:12:49,418 --> 00:12:50,456
We'll be invincible with this.

412
00:12:50,457 --> 00:12:51,516
- All right. Everyone.
- Okay.

413
00:12:51,517 --> 00:12:52,517
- This.
- Let's try it.

414
00:12:52,518 --> 00:12:53,757
- Go ahead.
- Can you roll it?

415
00:12:54,227 --> 00:12:55,426
I can roll it here?

416
00:12:55,427 --> 00:12:56,956
- Let's focus.
- Focus.

417
00:12:56,957 --> 00:12:58,526
- Let's roll a three and finish it.
- All right.

418
00:12:58,527 --> 00:13:00,267
Use your passion to roll a three.

419
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:01,697
- Use your passion.
- Passion.

420
00:13:01,867 --> 00:13:02,966
The mission got hard with Level Two.

421
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:04,137
- What's going on?
- Focus.

422
00:13:05,597 --> 00:13:07,336
(Inserting passion into the dice)

423
00:13:07,337 --> 00:13:08,817
- There it is.
- What did he just do?

424
00:13:09,207 --> 00:13:11,737
- He told it to focus. "Focus."
- I don't know why, but...

425
00:13:12,207 --> 00:13:14,207
I don't know why, but I think he can roll a three.

426
00:13:15,007 --> 00:13:17,216
He scolded the numbers on the dice to focus.

427
00:13:17,217 --> 00:13:18,217
- I'll do it.
- My gosh.

428
00:13:18,517 --> 00:13:19,517
Here it goes.

429
00:13:19,518 --> 00:13:20,846
- Let's go.
- Get ready.

430
00:13:20,847 --> 00:13:22,547
- Get ready.
- It's a three.

431
00:13:22,887 --> 00:13:24,016
- What is it?
- It's a three!

432
00:13:24,017 --> 00:13:25,017
- It's a two.
- Hey.

433
00:13:25,018 --> 00:13:27,126
- Jae Jun, come here.
- It's a two.

434
00:13:27,127 --> 00:13:28,456
- After you.
- It's us two.

435
00:13:28,457 --> 00:13:30,197
I'll do the handstand and lean against you.

436
00:13:30,357 --> 00:13:31,756
- Do the handstand.
- We have to do the handstand.

437
00:13:31,757 --> 00:13:33,167
- Lean against me.
- Yes.

438
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:34,367
- What?
- My gosh.

439
00:13:35,097 --> 00:13:36,636
- What about me?
- Lean against Jae Jun.

440
00:13:36,637 --> 00:13:38,566
Lean against me.

441
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:39,666
- I'll do it.
- Okay.

442
00:13:39,667 --> 00:13:41,437
- Here I go. One, two, three.
- Yes.

443
00:13:42,707 --> 00:13:43,736
Okay.

444
00:13:43,737 --> 00:13:44,737
- Are we good?
- We're good.

445
00:13:44,738 --> 00:13:45,906
- Not yet.
- One, two, three.

446
00:13:45,907 --> 00:13:47,076
- Get ready, Jae Jun.
- Okay.

447
00:13:47,077 --> 00:13:48,647
- Ready, set, go.
- One, two, three.

448
00:13:49,877 --> 00:13:51,777
(Only 2 legs are touching the floor at last.)

449
00:13:52,817 --> 00:13:55,317
Three, two, one.

450
00:13:56,047 --> 00:13:57,286
- Level Two is complete.
- We did it.

451
00:13:57,287 --> 00:13:58,617
- Okay. We did it.
- Okay.

452
00:13:58,957 --> 00:14:00,627
Gosh, that was easy.

453
00:14:01,027 --> 00:14:02,756
- That was easy.
- Oh, my wrists.

454
00:14:02,757 --> 00:14:04,196
(It's tough on the men in their 40s.)

455
00:14:04,197 --> 00:14:05,597
Level Two was quite tough.

456
00:14:06,257 --> 00:14:08,966
Will you try the next level?

457
00:14:08,967 --> 00:14:11,136
We said we'd go worldwide. Let's at least make it a triple.

458
00:14:11,137 --> 00:14:12,496
- Yes.
- We have five chances left.

459
00:14:12,497 --> 00:14:14,466
- So we're going worldwide? Okay.
- We ought to go for it.

460
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:16,106
- It's a team game.
- Completing Level Three...

461
00:14:16,107 --> 00:14:19,307
will win you salted oysters, Chungcheong Province's local dish...

462
00:14:19,477 --> 00:14:21,046
- And there's more.
- There's more.

463
00:14:21,047 --> 00:14:22,646
And gamtae, harvested from clean mudflats...

464
00:14:22,647 --> 00:14:24,076
- of the west coast.
- Gamtae.

465
00:14:24,077 --> 00:14:25,246
- Okay.
- Gosh.

466
00:14:25,247 --> 00:14:26,517
- That's good.
- Not bad.

467
00:14:26,717 --> 00:14:29,087
Your mission for Level Three...

468
00:14:29,247 --> 00:14:31,156
will be Yunho's solo mission.

469
00:14:31,157 --> 00:14:32,877
- His solo mission?
- What? A solo mission?

470
00:14:33,157 --> 00:14:35,387
- He can do it. He never fails.
- What is it?

471
00:14:36,227 --> 00:14:37,956
We were inspired...

472
00:14:37,957 --> 00:14:39,697
by the happy-birthday meme Yunho started.

473
00:14:39,997 --> 00:14:43,197
(Yunho started another popular meme in 2011.)

474
00:14:43,537 --> 00:14:44,766
(Happy birthday, Chang Min!)

475
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:46,396
(A surprise event on stage)

476
00:14:46,397 --> 00:14:48,367
It's called Happy Birthday.

477
00:14:48,707 --> 00:14:49,707
What's that?

478
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:52,506
He must pull out the table cloth in one go...

479
00:14:52,507 --> 00:14:54,506
without messing up the birthday table.

480
00:14:54,507 --> 00:14:55,677
He can totally do it.

481
00:14:55,807 --> 00:14:58,246
- I've done this a lot.
- Okay.

482
00:14:58,247 --> 00:14:59,846
I was basically in charge of this game.

483
00:14:59,847 --> 00:15:02,246
You shouldn't pull up the table cloth.

484
00:15:02,247 --> 00:15:04,286
You have to pull it down like it's falling off the table.

485
00:15:04,287 --> 00:15:05,816
So lower your body first.

486
00:15:05,817 --> 00:15:07,126
(He understands the logic.)

487
00:15:07,127 --> 00:15:09,047
- Right. Practicing sounds good.
- Pull it down.

488
00:15:09,187 --> 00:15:10,756
- Like this?
- You must do it in a flash.

489
00:15:10,757 --> 00:15:12,557
- Like this?
- Quickly. You're a dancer.

490
00:15:13,567 --> 00:15:15,166
- You got the idea.
