Car Escape Number One.

1467
00:47:09,386 --> 00:47:10,845
- "Car Escape?"
- Yes.

1468
00:47:10,846 --> 00:47:12,086
It's a team mission.

1469
00:47:12,586 --> 00:47:13,615
- Really?
- Yes.

1470
00:47:13,616 --> 00:47:15,286
You have 15 minutes...

1471
00:47:15,486 --> 00:47:17,186
to find seven alphabet cushions...

1472
00:47:17,786 --> 00:47:21,025
hidden at random spots while dodging the CCTVs...

1473
00:47:21,026 --> 00:47:24,596
and complete the word. If you succeed, you all will sleep indoors.

1474
00:47:25,296 --> 00:47:27,535
There are three CCTVs in total.

1475
00:47:27,536 --> 00:47:30,266
There's one CCTV camera monitoring each row between the cars.

1476
00:47:30,636 --> 00:47:34,176
(CCTV 1 monitoring Area 1)

1477
00:47:34,436 --> 00:47:37,976
(CCTV 2 monitoring Area 2)

1478
00:47:38,346 --> 00:47:41,976
(CCTV 3 monitoring Area 3)

1479
00:47:42,146 --> 00:47:45,345
The CCTV cameras capture a snapshot every six seconds.

1480
00:47:45,346 --> 00:47:46,486
Every six seconds?

1481
00:47:46,916 --> 00:47:48,615
Other than the three CCTV cameras,

1482
00:47:48,616 --> 00:47:51,586
there are more cameras hidden in a few cars.

1483
00:47:51,686 --> 00:47:54,995
So you have to dodge the hidden cameras as well.

1484
00:47:54,996 --> 00:47:57,625
The number of times you're caught on cameras will determine...

1485
00:47:57,626 --> 00:47:59,566
how many members sleep outdoors.

1486
00:47:59,866 --> 00:48:01,265
If you're caught on cameras six times or more...

1487
00:48:01,266 --> 00:48:03,665
or if you fail to complete the keyword within the time limit,

1488
00:48:03,666 --> 00:48:05,226
all of you will have to sleep outdoors.

1489
00:48:06,906 --> 00:48:08,505
And among all those cars,

1490
00:48:08,506 --> 00:48:11,675
- some of them are locked.
- Of course.

1491
00:48:11,676 --> 00:48:12,705
- Oh, gosh.
- Really?

1492
00:48:12,706 --> 00:48:14,375
Also, only the rear automatic doors...

1493
00:48:14,376 --> 00:48:17,085
- are accessible.
- My gosh.

1494
00:48:17,086 --> 00:48:19,145
- It takes six seconds to open.
- It takes time.

1495
00:48:19,146 --> 00:48:20,785
- That's correct.
- It takes a long time.

1496
00:48:20,786 --> 00:48:21,915
It's quite slow.

1497
00:48:21,916 --> 00:48:23,625
- We should leave after opening one.
- That's right.

1498
00:48:23,626 --> 00:48:24,985
And then we should think of the next move.

1499
00:48:24,986 --> 00:48:25,986
- That's right.
- Right.

1500
00:48:25,987 --> 00:48:27,955
You will be divided into 2 teams of 3.

1501
00:48:27,956 --> 00:48:30,666
You will be tethered together and will set off at the same time.

1502
00:48:30,796 --> 00:48:31,796
This sounds so difficult.

1503
00:48:31,797 --> 00:48:32,865
You'll be moving in teams of three.

1504
00:48:32,866 --> 00:48:34,765
You'll have to work together well while being tethered together.

1505
00:48:34,766 --> 00:48:36,465
- It sounds so difficult.
- Six seconds? It's so tough.

1506
00:48:36,466 --> 00:48:37,906
Listen to me.

1507
00:48:38,036 --> 00:48:40,305
In my opinion, we should split into an ace team...

1508
00:48:40,306 --> 00:48:41,905
and a second-best team.

1509
00:48:41,906 --> 00:48:43,145
- I agree.
- Really?

1510
00:48:43,146 --> 00:48:45,375
- Yunho, DinDin, - The quickest ones should be...

1511
00:48:45,376 --> 00:48:46,775
- and Joon are the ace team.
- Right.

1512
00:48:46,776 --> 00:48:48,315
- That's good.
- Come over here.

1513
00:48:48,316 --> 00:48:49,375
I'm on your team?

1514
00:48:49,376 --> 00:48:50,576
You're obviously on this team.

1515
00:48:50,616 --> 00:48:51,916
Don't look down on us.

1516
00:48:52,616 --> 00:48:54,255
The horizontal distance is shorter.

1517
00:48:54,256 --> 00:48:56,186
- Right.
- You guys move horizontally.

1518
00:48:56,456 --> 00:48:58,185
Your team moves horizontally.

1519
00:48:58,186 --> 00:48:59,595
I think we can move vertically.

1520
00:48:59,596 --> 00:49:00,596
Oh, you guys? Right.

1521
00:49:00,597 --> 00:49:03,295
So while we're checking the cars here,

1522
00:49:03,296 --> 00:49:05,165
you guys should move horizontally and check the cars here.

1523
00:49:05,166 --> 00:49:07,795
If we find cushions,

1524
00:49:07,796 --> 00:49:09,796
let's put them all in these two cars in the front.

1525
00:49:09,936 --> 00:49:11,135
Let's put them all in them.

1526
00:49:11,136 --> 00:49:13,675
- Just carry it around with you.
- Carry it around?

1527
00:49:13,676 --> 00:49:16,845
At the end, we'll gather around here with the cushions we found.

1528
00:49:16,846 --> 00:49:18,422
- We should minimize our movement.
- Exactly.

1529
00:49:18,446 --> 00:49:19,776
In the end...

1530
00:49:20,546 --> 00:49:22,275
This will be a hard game to win.

1531
00:49:22,276 --> 00:49:23,315
It won't be easy.

1532
00:49:23,316 --> 00:49:25,636
Exactly. It's not possible for all of us to sleep indoors.

1533
00:49:26,186 --> 00:49:28,686
(Despite the heavy security, )

1534
00:49:29,586 --> 00:49:33,495
(will they be able to complete the mission?)

1535
00:49:33,496 --> 00:49:35,096
- Are you ready?
- Yes!

1536
00:49:35,696 --> 00:49:36,925
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

1537
00:49:36,926 --> 00:49:38,895
- This is our last hope.
- Let's hold on to our last hope.

1538
00:49:38,896 --> 00:49:40,736
- Let's go.
- Where will we go?

1539
00:49:40,896 --> 00:49:42,366
2 Days 1 Night. Where will we go?

1540
00:49:42,496 --> 00:49:44,405
- To the world!
- To the world!

1541
00:49:44,406 --> 00:49:45,406
(To the world!)

1542
00:49:45,407 --> 00:49:47,275
To the world! Let's go!

1543
00:49:47,276 --> 00:49:48,276
Let's do this!

1544
00:49:49,476 --> 00:49:51,146
(Siren wailing)

1545
00:49:51,346 --> 00:49:54,546
(The siren goes off to signal the start of the mission.)

1546
00:49:55,846 --> 00:49:56,846
Here we go.

1547
00:49:56,847 --> 00:49:58,986
- Guys.
- Focus.

1548
00:49:59,386 --> 00:50:03,185
(They're very nervous as it's about to begin.)

1549
00:50:03,186 --> 00:50:04,655
- Here we go.
- Let's go.

1550
00:50:04,656 --> 00:50:05,886
Go. Move.

1551
00:50:06,186 --> 00:50:07,395
- Go.
- Let's go.

1552
00:50:07,396 --> 00:50:10,266
(They must hurry up and find 7 cushions.)

1553
00:50:10,496 --> 00:50:11,496
(Getting in the car quickly)

1554
00:50:11,497 --> 00:50:12,766
- Four.
- We have enough time.

1555
00:50:13,136 --> 00:50:14,196
Sit down.

1556
00:50:14,236 --> 00:50:15,965
(The younger guys get in the car quickly as well.)

1557
00:50:15,966 --> 00:50:17,805
- It's tight. We might not succeed.
- The time is tighter than expected.

1558
00:50:17,806 --> 00:50:18,835
I don't think we can find them here.

1559
00:50:18,836 --> 00:50:19,876
Nothing inside, right?

1560
00:50:20,306 --> 00:50:21,906
Don't we have to look it up?

1561
00:50:22,106 --> 00:50:23,106
Let's check the backseat.

1562
00:50:23,876 --> 00:50:26,546
(Searching thoroughly)

1563
00:50:26,646 --> 00:50:27,946
It's not here. It can't be here.

1564
00:50:28,046 --> 00:50:29,115
(The first van has no cushions.)

1565
00:50:29,116 --> 00:50:30,445
- It's not here.
- Right.

1566
00:50:30,446 --> 00:50:31,515
Is it not there in the front seat?

1567
00:50:31,516 --> 00:50:33,516
- Get ready.
- Don't get down yet.

1568
00:50:34,656 --> 00:50:35,785
(Planning to move to the next van)

1569
00:50:35,786 --> 00:50:37,726
I'll push it and come back.

1570
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:40,395
Don't come, turn back.

1571
00:50:40,396 --> 00:50:43,326
(Returning to the van after opening the door)

1572
00:50:45,296 --> 00:50:47,136
(No issues)

1573
00:50:47,436 --> 00:50:48,566
Why didn't it open?

1574
00:50:49,436 --> 00:50:50,605
(The door of the van won't open?)

1575
00:50:50,606 --> 00:50:52,206
- This van's door won't open.
- Hold on.

1576
00:50:52,266 --> 00:50:54,105
Let's try it again.

1577
00:50:54,106 --> 00:50:55,675
(Getting down to open it again)

1578
00:50:55,676 --> 00:50:57,106
- Okay.
- It won't open.

1579
00:50:57,706 --> 00:50:59,075
- Okay.
- It won't open.

1580
00:50:59,076 --> 00:51:00,775
(It turns out they picked the van that is locked.)

1581
00:51:00,776 --> 00:51:02,415
- We have to go diagonally.
- So it's a trap.

1582
00:51:02,416 --> 00:51:04,186
(They picked a locked van of all the vans.)

1583
00:51:04,646 --> 00:51:07,186
(Time's ticking, but they're back to square one.)

1584
00:51:07,216 --> 00:51:08,385
Let's cut across and then come back.

1585
00:51:08,386 --> 00:51:09,685
We go diagonally and come back.

1586
00:51:09,686 --> 00:51:11,226
- Diagonally.
- All right, ready?

1587
00:51:11,726 --> 00:51:13,126
- We'll go diagonally.
- All right.

1588
00:51:15,656 --> 00:51:16,765
- Run!
- Run.

1589
00:51:16,766 --> 00:51:18,026
(Running)

1590
00:51:19,426 --> 00:51:20,596
- Okay.
- Good.

1591
00:51:20,836 --> 00:51:22,195
- Did it open?
- It did.

1592
00:51:22,196 --> 00:51:23,205
- We'll get inside the van now.
- Okay.

1593
00:51:23,206 --> 00:51:24,765
(They opened the door this time.)

1594
00:51:24,766 --> 00:51:25,806
Ready?

1595
00:51:26,166 --> 00:51:27,935
(Quickly running toward the van with the door open)

1596
00:51:27,936 --> 00:51:29,606
(Joon's camera)

1597
00:51:32,576 --> 00:51:33,746
Here it is.

1598
00:51:34,076 --> 00:51:35,475
- It's here.
- It's here.

1599
00:51:35,476 --> 00:51:37,086
- Search for it.
- Let's start.

1600
00:51:37,486 --> 00:51:38,545
Search.

1601
00:51:38,546 --> 00:51:40,515
(Search begins.)

1602
00:51:40,516 --> 00:51:41,516
It's not in the front seat.

1603
00:51:41,516 --> 00:51:42,516
It's not in the back seat either.

1604
00:51:42,517 --> 00:51:43,655
They said they didn't leave it in the front seat.

1605
00:51:43,656 --> 00:51:44,726
It's not here.

1606
00:51:44,786 --> 00:51:45,855
(It's getting tricky.)

1607
00:51:45,856 --> 00:51:47,432
- So it's not here.
- It's not here, right?

1608
00:51:47,456 --> 00:51:49,925
(What's happening to the older guys?)

1609
00:51:49,926 --> 00:51:51,395
Hold on a second. We'll get going now.

1610
00:51:51,396 --> 00:51:53,442
- I'll run to the next van.
- No, wait. It hasn't started.

1611
00:51:53,466 --> 00:51:55,095
- You'll drop it.
- You'll drop it.

1612
00:51:55,096 --> 00:51:56,096
(They'll target the van next to theirs.)

1613
00:51:56,097 --> 00:51:57,542
Hold on. I'll start running when I get down.

1614
00:51:57,566 --> 00:51:58,965
(Getting nervous)

1615
00:51:58,966 --> 00:52:00,505
- Wait.
- Don't we have to go now?

1616
00:52:00,506 --> 00:52:01,575
Hold on a second.

1617
00:52:01,576 --> 00:52:02,705
Let's do it again.

1618
00:52:02,706 --> 00:52:04,545
- I told you to stay calm.
- No, let me handle this.

1619
00:52:04,546 --> 00:52:05,845
- What do you mean by that?
- No, look.

1620
00:52:05,846 --> 00:52:07,415
How many times are you hesitating?

1621
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:09,615
- I'll go this time.
- Stop hesitating.

1622
00:52:09,616 --> 00:52:10,745
I'll get back to the van right after I open the door.

1623
00:52:10,746 --> 00:52:11,746
- I'll get back here again.
- Just go!

1624
00:52:11,747 --> 00:52:13,216
Go! I heard the flash!

1625
00:52:13,356 --> 00:52:14,515
I'll open the door at the count.

1626
00:52:14,516 --> 00:52:15,586
Come on.

1627
00:52:15,656 --> 00:52:17,085
I said I'll run at the count!

1628
00:52:17,086 --> 00:52:18,755
- They already counted.
- Why wouldn't you go?

1629
00:52:18,756 --> 00:52:21,025
I said I'll go at the count!

1630
00:52:21,026 --> 00:52:22,525
- You have to go now.
- I'll go at the next sign.

1631
00:52:22,526 --> 00:52:23,765
- You'll waste more time?
- Jae Jun.

1632
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:25,826
What are you doing? This is the first one!

1633
00:52:25,996 --> 00:52:27,195
- What?
- Let's go!

1634
00:52:27,196 --> 00:52:28,735
(They finally departed.)

1635
00:52:28,736 --> 00:52:29,806
Go back.

1636
00:52:30,066 --> 00:52:32,406
(They ended up opening the door.)

1637
00:52:33,006 --> 00:52:35,636
(They have to get back without their photo taken.)

1638
00:52:36,306 --> 00:52:38,545
(They almost got shot.)

1639
00:52:38,546 --> 00:52:39,816
All right.

1640
00:52:39,916 --> 00:52:40,916
I see something there.

1641
00:52:41,316 --> 00:52:42,376
Go!

1642
00:52:42,846 --> 00:52:43,916
Hurry up.

1643
00:52:44,286 --> 00:52:45,286
Hurry up now.

1644
00:52:45,916 --> 00:52:46,956
Okay.

1645
00:52:47,486 --> 00:52:48,555
- We made it.
- Goodness.

1646
00:52:48,556 --> 00:52:49,656
Search for it.

1647
00:52:49,986 --> 00:52:52,485
(After a series of twists and turns, they made it to the next van.)

1648
00:52:52,486 --> 00:52:53,595
- We're here.
- My gosh.

1649
00:52:53,596 --> 00:52:55,095
- Search it.
- Press it.

1650
00:52:55,096 --> 00:52:56,496
Look for the cushions.

1651
00:52:56,896 --> 00:52:58,496
Can we have this snack?

1652
00:52:58,766 --> 00:52:59,766
Can I eat this?

1653
00:52:59,767 --> 00:53:01,435
(He found a snack instead of cushions.)

1654
00:53:01,436 --> 00:53:03,505
(He's so hungry that he doesn't care about the cushions.)

1655
00:53:03,506 --> 00:53:05,106
I'm so hungry. All I had was just rice.

1656
00:53:05,366 --> 00:53:06,635
Look for the cushion.

1657
00:53:06,636 --> 00:53:07,806
No cushion here?

1658
00:53:08,576 --> 00:53:11,606
(They found 0 cushion even after 2 minutes and 30 seconds.)

1659
00:53:11,876 --> 00:53:13,045
This isn't bad at all.

1660
00:53:13,046 --> 00:53:14,246
Let's get going.

1661
00:53:14,516 --> 00:53:15,775
I'll move first.

1662
00:53:15,776 --> 00:53:17,536
(They are planning to move to the next van.)

1663
00:53:19,386 --> 00:53:20,715
(Quickly moving in order)

1664
00:53:20,716 --> 00:53:22,516
I found it.

1665
00:53:23,656 --> 00:53:24,656
You saw something?

1666
00:53:24,657 --> 00:53:26,185
(They finally found a cushion.)

1667
00:53:26,186 --> 00:53:27,455
- Where?
- Okay.

1668
00:53:27,456 --> 00:53:28,596
- It's "S."
- Right.

1669
00:53:28,696 --> 00:53:30,242
- Where shall we go next?
- This is "S."

1670
00:53:30,266 --> 00:53:31,595
Yunho wants to go in that van.

1671
00:53:31,596 --> 00:53:32,995
- Diagonally.
- Right, diagonally.

1672
00:53:32,996 --> 00:53:34,665
- Then we come back the same way.
- Right.

1673
00:53:34,666 --> 00:53:36,706
We'll come back to this van after opening the door.

1674
00:53:39,106 --> 00:53:40,135
It's open.

1675
00:53:40,136 --> 00:53:42,256
(Getting back to the same van after opening the door)

1676
00:53:43,246 --> 00:53:46,106
- Gosh.
- This is how we run next time.

1677
00:53:48,316 --> 00:53:49,515
(Joon's camera)

1678
00:53:49,516 --> 00:53:51,316
(Running towards the target)

1679
00:53:52,086 --> 00:53:53,616
- Okay.
- I see another one.

1680
00:53:54,716 --> 00:53:56,155
(They found one more cushion in a row.)

1681
00:53:56,156 --> 00:53:57,156
What?

1682
00:53:57,157 --> 00:53:58,726
- It's "I."
- So we have "S" and "I."

1683
00:53:59,286 --> 00:54:00,696
- "S."
- "I."

1684
00:54:00,826 --> 00:54:01,956
We'll go to the right van.

1685
00:54:02,796 --> 00:54:04,265
I'll throw this then.

1686
00:54:04,266 --> 00:54:05,466
I'll throw this one.

1687
00:54:05,496 --> 00:54:08,295
This is actually fun.

1688
00:54:08,296 --> 00:54:09,595
I'm so scared.

1689
00:54:09,596 --> 00:54:10,665
Let's go.

1690
00:54:10,666 --> 00:54:11,666
Go, hurry now.

1691
00:54:11,666 --> 00:54:12,666
(Quickly moving to the next van)

1692
00:54:12,667 --> 00:54:13,706
Hurry up now!

1693
00:54:14,936 --> 00:54:16,435
Look for the cushion.

1694
00:54:16,436 --> 00:54:18,045
- I mean this...
- Look for the cushion.

1695
00:54:18,046 --> 00:54:19,876
Look at the floor.

1696
00:54:20,376 --> 00:54:21,376
Check the floor.

1697
00:54:21,676 --> 00:54:22,922
I don't see anything on the floor.

1698
00:54:22,946 --> 00:54:24,146
I don't see any cushions.

1699
00:54:24,716 --> 00:54:25,716
No cushions?

1700
00:54:25,717 --> 00:54:26,755
(Unlike the younger guys, they found none.)

1701
00:54:26,756 --> 00:54:28,086
Where do we go next?

1702
00:54:28,216 --> 00:54:29,536
We'll go to the van in the front.

1703
00:54:29,716 --> 00:54:30,785
We have to go to the van in the front.

1704
00:54:30,786 --> 00:54:33,055
I'll go and open the door of the van in front of us...

1705
00:54:33,056 --> 00:54:34,256
on the next attempt.

1706
00:54:34,426 --> 00:54:35,756
- Okay.
- I'll be quick.

1707
00:54:36,156 --> 00:54:37,625
Sure, you should go now.

1708
00:54:37,626 --> 00:54:39,425
- No, you can't go now.
- You should go.

1709
00:54:39,426 --> 00:54:40,912
- Don't go now.
- You should come to the back.

1710
00:54:40,936 --> 00:54:42,435
- You can't go now.
- I'll go now.

1711
00:54:42,436 --> 00:54:43,565
(Getting nervous)

1712
00:54:43,566 --> 00:54:46,306
You have to open the door at the flash and come back.

1713
00:54:47,876 --> 00:54:49,476
Open the door and come back.

1714
00:54:49,506 --> 00:54:51,276
(Suddenly slapstick)

1715
00:54:51,346 --> 00:54:54,276
(Pulling himself together and rushing towards the van)

1716
00:54:55,176 --> 00:54:57,686
(They got shot together.)

1717
00:54:58,146 --> 00:55:00,116
